hands_on_practices.introduction:
The power of the Bochner technique originates from the Weitzenböck formula, $\Delta = 
abla^{*}
abla + \mathcal{R}_{p}$, which relates the Hodge Laplacian $\Delta$ to the connection Laplacian $
abla^{*}
abla$ and a "curvature" term $\mathcal{R}_{p}$. This first exercise [@problem_id:2993002] takes you to the heart of the technique by having you compute this crucial curvature operator for $p$-forms on a manifold of constant sectional curvature $K$. Mastering this foundational calculation reveals how geometric curvature is translated into an algebraic operator, whose positivity is the key to proving vanishing theorems.
